'''Lee Albon''' is an [[Australians|Australian]] former [[cricket]] player, born 7 November 1959 in [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria, Australia|Victoria]].<ref name="ESPNcricinfo - Lee Albon - Australia">{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/53590.html|title=Lee Albon - Australia|work=[[ESPNcricinfo]]|publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]]|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref> Albon played four [[One Day International|one day internationals]] for the [[Australia national women's cricket team]].<ref name="ESPNcricinfo - Lee Albon - Australia"/>

Albon played as an [[Batting order (cricket)#Opening batsmen|opening bat]] with the [[Victorian state women's cricket team]].<ref name="The Age - 24 January 1980 - Vics have the edge">{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1300&dat=19800124&id=Yu5UAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lpIDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5629,3589585|title=Vics have the edge|last=[[Peg McMahon]]|date=24 January 1980|work=[[The Age]]|publisher=[[Fairfax Media]]|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

